story: James and Emma were neighbors. James was loud and loved parties. Emma was quiet and liked books. One day, James threw a wild party. The music was so loud Emma could hear it in her house. She tried to read but couldn’t focus. Emma decided to go over and ask James to turn it down. When she knocked, James opened the door with a big smile. “Join the fun!” he said. Emma said no thanks but asked if he could lower the music. James agreed and turned it down a little. Emma went back home happy. The next day, James saw Emma outside. He apologized for the noise. Emma said it was okay and invited him for tea. James was surprised but went. They talked and laughed. From that day, James was quieter, and Emma didn’t mind his small parties. They became good friends. The end.
